    {
      "id": "311faeaf-0d05-4293-b175-8512dcb56669",
      "name": "Note: Overview",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "position": [
        -3600,
        -176
      ],
      "parameters": {
        "width": 660,
        "height": 600,
        "content": "## Migrate Categories: Lightspeed to Shopify\n\nAutomatically migrates all visible product categories from Lightspeed to Shopify:\n- Creates Shopify collections with title, description, SEO metadata, and images\n- Sets up URL redirects from old Lightspeed paths to new Shopify collection URLs\n- Publishes collections to all active sales channels\n\n**How it works**\n1. Fetches all publication channels from your Shopify store\n2. Retrieves categories from the Lightspeed API\n3. Filters out hidden/invisible categories\n4. For each visible category: creates a collection, sets up a redirect, and publishes it\n\n**Setup instructions**\n- [ ] Update the \"Configure store settings\" node with your Shopify store URL and Lightspeed API URL\n- [ ] Create a **Header Auth** credential with header name `X-Shopify-Access-Token` and your Shopify Admin API access token as value. Assign it to all four Shopify HTTP Request nodes.\n- [ ] Create a **Basic Auth** credential with your Lightspeed API key and secret. Assign it to the \"Fetch Lightspeed categories\" node.\n- [ ] Run the workflow manually."
      },
      "typeVersion": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "e661f246-2c55-4e5a-b8a2-e998eaadcd91",
      "name": "Note: Setup",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "position": [
        -2896,
        -176
      ],
      "parameters": {
        "color": 7,
        "width": 436,
        "height": 432,
        "content": "### 1. Setup & Configuration\nConfigure your store URLs and API version here. Credentials are managed via n8n's credential system (Header Auth for Shopify, Basic Auth for Lightspeed)."
      },
      "typeVersion": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "95aa337f-c95d-47aa-a114-0a03bb28996f",
      "name": "Note: Fetch Data",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "position": [
        -2432,
        -176
      ],
      "parameters": {
        "color": 7,
        "width": 804,
        "height": 432,
        "content": "### 2. Fetch Data\nRetrieves Shopify publication channels (for publishing later) and all Lightspeed categories. Only visible categories pass through to the migration loop."
      },
      "typeVersion": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "a55df075-7a6e-4fbc-82c7-a56de923d884",
      "name": "Note: Migration Loop",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "position": [
        -1600,
        -176
      ],
      "parameters": {
        "color": 7,
        "width": 1688,
        "height": 624,
        "content": "### 3. Migrate Each Category\nFor each visible Lightspeed category: creates a Shopify collection via GraphQL, sets up a URL redirect (old path to new /collections/ URL), and publishes the collection to all sales channels. Stops on any Shopify API error."
      },
      "typeVersion": 1
    }
